    ####  1.2.1 - 2015.03.29

    * Fix Autocompletion when using IPython3 [#1351](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1351).
 
    ####  1.2 - 2015.03.27

    * Support Scala and Java, including sharing classes with Groovy.
    * Support running Python2 and Python3 at the same time, even with different versions of IPython [#776](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/776).
    * Allow user to select location of language backend from their beaker.prefs.json file, as well as the options passed to it [#1166](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1166).
    * Works with IPython3 (in addtion to 1 and 2) [#1222](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1222).
    * Works with Mac OS 10.6 and 10.7 [#408](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/408).
    * Works on Macs with old chipsets [#398](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/398), [#982](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/982).
    * Better error reporting from missing backend [#1180](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1180), [#880](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/880), 
    * New API for progress reporting during cell evaluation [#910](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/910).
    * New API for fullscreen dashboards [#1025](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1025).
    * New API for reflection (access to other cells source code and results) and control (cell evaluation can trigger evaluation of other cells).
    * Standard output and error output now appear below the cell that produced them instead of in a unified panel [#667](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/667), [#937](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/937).
    * Add tutorial for loading external JavaScript libraries, in particular p5.js [#1176](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1176).
    * Allow sharing and saving `<canvas>` elements [#1075](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1075).
    * Handle installation and user paths with spaces [#931](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/931).
    * Fix JavaScript injection problem on shared notebooks [#862](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/862).
    * New View menu item "close all sections" [#872](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/872).
    * Upload notebooks with native file dialog or drag-and-drop [#830](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/830), [#857](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/857), [#1116](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1116).
    * Improved Language Manager UI.
    * Use scss to improve modularity of styles [#1071](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1071).
    * Support ipynb section headings during import [#1015](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1015).
    * Subsections numbered from 1 instead of 0 [#629](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/629).
    * Groovy evaluation is interruptible [#560](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/560).
    * Add progress indicator to sharing [#383](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/383).
    * UI for tagging cells [#403](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/403).
    * R plots made with ggplot2 work on Firefox [#987](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/987)
    * On Windows find R via the registry instead of the PATH [#1178](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1178).
    * Improved file open and save dialogs [#904](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/904), [#1016](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1016), [#1017](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1017), [#1061](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1061), [#1158](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1158), [#1159](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1159), [#1161](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1161).
    * Massive UI polish [#672](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/672), [#673](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/673), [#747](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/747), [#772](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/772), [#819](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/819), [#854](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/854), [#856](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/856), [#874](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/874), [#902](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/902), [#906](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/906), [#968](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/968), [#970](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/970), [#972](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/972), [#990](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/990), [#1027](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1027), [#1045](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1045), [#1047](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1047), [#1053](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1053), [#1062](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1062), [#1070](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1070), [#1119](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1119), [#1130](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1130), [#1139](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/1139).

    ####  1.1.2 - 2014.11.5

    * Fix problem where a missing backend prevents the whole notebook from loading [#836](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/836), [#845](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/845)
    * And on 2014.11.11 made a new build of windows, still version 1.1.2 but packaged correctly to fix [#853](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/853)
    * And on 2015.01.16 made a new build of mac, still version 1.1.2 but with a hotfix for [#824](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/824)

    ####  1.1.1 - 2014.10.31

    * Fix problem with defining functions in R [#827](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/827)

    ####  1.1 - 2014.10.30

    * New table (dataframe) display [#716](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/716), [#717](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/717), [#735](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/735), [#432](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/432), [#270](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/270), [#760](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/760), [#777](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/777)
    * Able to open larger notebooks without freezing by loading plugins before rendering the notebook (however the downside of this is you can't see the notebook while the plugins load) [#751](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/pull/751)
    * Most keyboard commands (especially command-enter to run the current cell) can now be accessed with command key, not just control (for Mac users) [#220](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/220), [#778](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/778)
    * Python3 support [#695](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/695), [#740](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/740)
    * Direct access to autotranslation in python without a function call (`beaker.x` instead of `beaker.get("x")`) [#675](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/675)
    * Add the ability to control the size of R plots [#707](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/707)
    * Correctly suppress invisible results from R [#232](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/232)
    * Add the ability to share d3 plots [#691](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/691)
    * Replace the d3 tutorial, various tutorial polish [#685](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/685), [#729](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/729), [#730](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/730), [#732](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/732), [#754](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/754), [#790](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/790)
    * Do not hide "falsey" evaluation results [#444](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/444)
    * Fixed Docker container port remapping and Python plugin [#702](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/702)
    * Sharing server now supports levels of detail and section toggling
    * Sharing server URL location is configurable [#769](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/769)
    * Fixed display of dataframes in python mangled by pandas groupby operation [#694](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/694)
    * Interaction state of plots and tables saved in the notebook and shareable [#413](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/413)
    * Remove deprecated --pylab option from IPython [#165](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/165)
    * When loading a plugin from a cross-origin URL, show a dialog warning the user that it could be unsafe [#144](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/144)
    * Better cache busting method (so you should not have to clear the cache when you upgrade Beaker) [#742](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/742)
    * Changed short name of Groovy from Gr to Gv [#687](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/687)
    * Avoid Java icon in dock [#688](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/688)
    * Improve plot handling of NaNs [#697](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/697)
    * New icon, favicon, and branding [#755](https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/issues/755)
    * Update JRE from 7u60 to 7u71
    
    ####  1.0 - 2014.09.24

    * Redesigned UI that is beautiful and easier to use.
    * Autotranslation of data between languages.
    * Interactive charting, including with levels-of-detail.
    * Docker container for easy deployment.
    * Detect when connection to server is lost and give extra chance to
      save the notebook.
    * Plugin manager allows removing languages from a notebook.
    * Security fix for Julia on multiuser systems.
    * Removed Ruby from plugin manager because it is insecure on
      multiuser systems (but it can still be added by entering its URL).
    * Rewrite tutorials.
    * Numerous bug fixes.
    * Groovy supports classpath to access JARS, and default imports.
    * R supports interrupting evaluations.


    ####  0.55 - 2014.07.17
    
    * Major upgrade of the security model: backends are now protected even on multi-user systems.
    * Add public server option so that you can access Beaker over the internet, not just locally. Includes HTTPS encryption.
    * Refactor the JavaScript to conform to Angular guidelines.
    * Improve file load/save dialogs to be easier to use and handle errors.
    * Shared notebooks can be downloaded from the resulting share page, and the sharing viewer can open a notebook file hosted anywhere.
    * On Mac, add a native application to wrap and launch the web app. The native app includes the JRE, eliminating an external dependency for users.
    * On Windows, include the JRE, nginx, and python in our distribution.
    * On Ubuntu, include a script to install all dependencies and language plugins.


    #### 0.52.4 - 2014.05.03

    * Security fix: close ports to external access.


    #### 0.52.1 - 2014.05.02

    * Fix loading nginx dynamic libraries on Mac.


    #### 0.52 - 2014.04.29

    * First public release.
